Step 1: Determine the average total assets.  
• Beginning total assets = 16,000,000.00  
• Ending total assets = 21,662,106.19  
• Average total assets = (16,000,000.00 + 21,662,106.19) / 2 = 18,831,053.095  

Step 2: Identify the total revenue.  
• Main Business Revenue (or Total Revenue) = 863,371.65  

Step 3: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.  
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• = 863,371.65 / 18,831,053.095  
• ≈ 0.04585, which rounds to 0.05  

Thus, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is 0.05.
